      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "To judge whether an RMSE or MAE value represents a large or small error, we express it as a percentage of the median salary rather than reading the raw dollar amount in isolation.\n",
        "\n",
        "For example, Model 1 RMSE being 32.1% of median salary means the model's typical prediction error ($36,527) is equivalent to about a third of the typical salary in our dataset ($113,800) -- a meaningful, non-trivial error.\n",
        "\n",
        "Since this gap is fairly large, we proceed to refine the model in Model 2, adding features and structure to try to close it."
      ],
